commText: Jaiswal and Buttler are at the crease. Jaiswal is on strike. Starc will open the attack
Starc to Jaiswal, wide, a wayward start from Starc, it's wide outside off and swings further away to cut the tramline. The keeper collects it in front of first slip
Starc to Jaiswal, 1 run, 141kph good length ball in the channel, Jaiswal punches it to squarish third man to get moving
Starc to Buttler, 1 run, skiddy good length ball on middle at 146.7kph, Buttler works it towards mid-on to get off the mark
Starc to Jaiswal, no run, shortish in length and width on offer, 142.7 clicks this time, Jaiswal slashes at it and misses
Starc to Jaiswal, FOUR, 144.3kph fuller length ball outside off, shaping away, Jaiswal clears his front leg and hits it over extra cover to get the desired result
Deep backward point in place now and third man comes inside the ring
Starc to Jaiswal, no run, 143.7kph fullish ball swinging away from around off, Jaiswal throws his bat at it but is beaten for pace

Starc to Jaiswal, FOUR, a pacy back of a length ball outside off, Jaiswal opens his bat-face and punches it past the left side of short third man. Deep backward point has no chance to cut it off. Good placement there
Vaibhav Arora, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Vaibhav Arora to Buttler, 1 run, fullish ball swinging in on off, Buttler eases it towards mid-on and scurries across to the other end
Vaibhav Arora to Jaiswal, no run, a full ball swinging towards the off-stump at 132.3kph, Jaiswal creams the drive but plays it straight to extra cover
Vaibhav Arora to Jaiswal, SIX, crunched! A fullish ball swinging away, Jaiswal clears his front leg and smashes it over long-off for a 82m maximum

Vaibhav Arora to Jaiswal, FOUR, just over the man at wide mid-on! A full ball on middle and leg, Jaiswal mistimes the flick to the left of the fielder. He moves around and leaps but it just evades his outstreched fingers. Chakravarthy the man there
Vaibhav Arora to Jaiswal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Vaibhav Arora to Jaiswal, out Caught by Venkatesh Iyer!! The round the wicket angle pays dividends for Vaibhav Arora and he is pumped up! He keeps it full around off, Jaiswal without moving his feet goes for an expansive shot down the ground but only manages to edge it behind. Venkatesh Iyer at wide slip takes it safely. Jaiswal c Venkatesh Iyer b Vaibhav Arora 19(9) [4s-3 6s-1]
Sanju Samson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Vaibhav Arora to Samson, 1 run, a full-toss outside off, Samson drives it to wide mid-off to get off the mark
Starc to Samson, 1 run, back of a length ball wide outside off, Samson cuts it past backward point to rotate strike
Starc to Buttler, FOUR, smashed! An overpitched delivery outside off, Buttler pounces on it and drills it past extra cover. The ball travels to the fence at the rate of knots
Starc to Buttler, wide, 145.5kph full ball wide outside off, cuts the tramline as Buttler lets it go
Starc to Buttler, no run, back of a length ball shaping across Buttler at 144.8kph, Buttler toe-ends the punch to backward point
Starc to Buttler, wide, a short ball down leg, Buttler goes for a pull half-heartedly but doesn't make any connection
Starc to Buttler, FOUR, shot! 137.7kph back of a length ball well outside off, Buttler punches it crisply. Finds the gap at covers and gets the desired result
Deep cover in place now
Starc to Buttler, 1 run, short of length ball well outside off, Buttler punches it to sweeper cover

Starc to Samson, 1 run, did it carry? A back of a length ball shaping across Samson. He throws his bat at it and gets a thick outside edge towards short third man. Chakravarthy there dives but the ball seemed to have just landed in front of him
Vaibhav Arora to Samson, FOUR, a full ball in the slot, Samson lofts it over mid-on for a boundary. Not off the meat of the bat but got enough on it
Long-on in place now
Vaibhav Arora to Samson, FOUR, fuller length ball outside off, Samson shuffles across his stumps and whips it over mid-wicket. Beats the fielder in the deep to his left with ease
Vaibhav Arora to Samson, 1 run, full ball swinging in on middle and leg, Samson pushes it towards long-on
Replays in on 2.6 and it certainly carried to Chakravarthy. Went right through his hands. How costly will that prove?
Vaibhav Arora to Buttler, no run, good length ball shaping in on off, Buttler pushes it back to Vaibhav Arora. Was cramped for room there
Vaibhav Arora to Buttler, 1 run, pitched up outside off, Buttler looks to flick it across but gets a leading edge past point

Vaibhav Arora to Samson, no run, 136.6kph full ball swinging in on off, Samson bunts it back to Vaibhav Arora. Good comeback from Arora after being hit for boundaries off the first two balls of this over
Harshit Rana, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshit Rana to Buttler, 1 run, 140.5kph length ball swinging in from outside off, Buttler pushes it off the inner half to mid-wicket
Harshit Rana to Samson, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to Samson, out Caught by Narine!! A soft dismissal! Narine gets into the act once again, this time with his fielding! A skiddy good length ball on off, Samson stays rooted to the crease and punches it tamely. Ends up mistiming it completely as the ball lobs towards mid-on. Narine backtracks, keeps his eyes on the ball, and makes no mistake. Samson c Narine b Harshit Rana 12(8) [4s-2]
Riyan Parag, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, no run, a pacy short ball outside off, Riyan Parag is late on the pull shot and misses
Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, no run, back of a length ball angling in sharply, Riyan Parag makes room and tries to upper cut it but misses
Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, wide, a slower fullish ball shaping down leg, wided

Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, FOUR, edged but safe! Riyan Parag makes room once again and Harshit Rana cramps him up with a length delivery. Riyan Parag looks to work it across but gets a leading edge past short third man for a boundary
Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, 1 run, good length ball shaping towards the pads, Riyan Parag whips it off the inner half to short fine

1-5 Over Summary: -- Jaiswal collects a couple of boundaries vs Starc -- 6 4 W - Vaibhav nips out Jaiswal -- 13 runs off Starc's 2nd over -- Samson dropped on 2 by Chakaravarthy; scores back-to-back fours after that -- RR's captain falls to Harshit Rana -- Rana troubles Parag but the latter gets off the mark with a streaky boundary

Vaibhav Arora to Riyan Parag, FOUR, nicely played! This shot will settle Riyan Parag's nerves. This time he stays still to the back of a length ball on the hips and tucks it nicely through backward square leg to find the fence
Vaibhav Arora to Riyan Parag, 1 run, full ball outside off, driven crisply towards extra cover and a fumble from the fielder allows the single
Vaibhav Arora to Buttler, no ball, a slower full ball floated towards leg-stump, Buttler looks to hit it across but is struck on the pads. Vaibhav Arora has overstepped, so a Free Hit coming up...
Vaibhav Arora to Buttler, SIX, a juicy full-toss on off, just what Buttler wanted and he launches it over long-on to clear the ropes
Vaibhav Arora to Buttler, 1 run, back of a length ball angling in, Buttler pulls it to deep backward square leg
Vaibhav Arora to Riyan Parag, SIX, smashed! A pitched up ball outside off, Riyan Parag lines it up and he smokes it over cow corner for a maximum. He was so balanced when he played that shot

Vaibhav Arora to Riyan Parag, FOUR, a half-volley outside off, Riyan Parag says thank you very much and drills the drive in the gap between mid-off and extra cover for another boundary. 23 runs off the over
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Spin time
Narine to Buttler, 1 run, 98.3kph, quick offie on the pads and that's been tickled to short fine leg
Narine to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, 97.8kph, another pad-lined ball, worked in front of square on the leg-side for a couple of runs
Narine to Riyan Parag, 2 wides, 96.6kph, spinning down leg from a short of length, Parag misses the heave and even the keeper can't stop it. The batters rotate strike

Highest powerplay scores for RR in the IPL 85/1 vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2023 81/1 vs CSK, Abu Dhabi, 2021 78/1 vs KKR, Kolkata, 2023 76/2 vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024 73/1 vs Deccan Chargers, Hyderabad, 2008 Four of the above five have come in run-chases.
Narine to Buttler, 2 runs, 100.2kph, in-dart on the stumps, knocked towards long-on
Narine to Buttler, leg byes, 1 run, 101.8kph, quick in-turner, Buttler is late on the glance and the ball rolls towards square leg off his pad
Narine to Riyan Parag, 1 run, 99.8kph, short of length, Parag pushes it to long-off
Narine to Buttler, no run, fuller ball just outside off, defensively pushed to extra cover

Strategic timeout! Both batsmen were watchful against Narine. However, RR decided to go after the other bowlers. Their scoring rate is more than asking rate and that's always a good position to be in while chasing. Can KKR choke the flow of runs with spin?
Harshit Rana [1.0-0-7-1] is back into the attack

Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, SIX, 140.7kph, he was backing away against Harshit Rana in the previous over. This time he stays still in his crease. It's a leg-lined length ball and Parag whips it away over backward square leg. Off the meat of the bat

Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, FOUR, foure more, this time through the off-side. Rana overcorrects and serves witdh, no feet movement from Riyan Parag but quick hands from the right-hander to slap the cut over backward point. Bullets away to the fence
Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, 1 run, slower delivery, Parag clears his front leg to hoick across the line and inside-edges to deep midwicket
Harshit Rana to Buttler, 1 run, 113.4kph, slower delivery from a short of length on leg, tickled to fine leg
Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Russell!! Harshit Rana has the last laugh against Riyan Parag! 113.7kph, off-cutter from Harshit Rana, fuller than a good length and the batsman thinks it's in his slot. Parag shuffles across a bit to flog it over cow corner. However, he's a bit rearly into his shot and the bat turns at the point of impact. More height than distance. Russell comes in from deep midwicket, watches it keenly and makes a tough catch look easy. Riyan Parag c Russell b Harshit Rana 34(14) [4s-4 6s-2]
Dhruv Jurel, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, short of length outside off, Dhruv Jurel runs it down to third man. 13 runs and a wicket off the over!
Narine to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, 96kph, bit of extra bounce from a length and that's been nudged into the leg-side for a single
Narine to Buttler, 1 run, 100.5kph, offie, Buttler goes back in his crease to hurriedly flick it towards midwicket
Narine to Dhruv Jurel, no run, 99.8kph, short of length outside off, cut straight to backward point
Narine to Dhruv Jurel, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Narine to Dhruv Jurel, out Lbw!! 97.8kph, appeal for lbw, turned down. Narine and Philip Salt are confident, Shreyas Iyer sends it upstairs. Impact could be the key here. Spinning offbreak, Jurel is half-forward to block and is beaten comprehensively on the inside edge. Clearly no bat and the batsman is struck on the back leg. The TV umpire doesn't even want to use UltraEdge. Ball-tracking in and it's three reds! KKR are cock-a-hoop. Impact - in front of off and HawkEye shows it to be hitting middle. Excellent review from KKR. Philip Salt straightaway signalled 'T' when the umpire turned it down. Dhruv Jurel lbw b Narine 2(4)
Ravichandran Ashwin, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Narine to Ashwin, wide, 97.7kph, spinning down leg, past Ashwin's glance and the batsman reviews it. Wide not given onfield. Did the ball brush Ashwin's pad on the way? Flat line on UltraEdge and it's a successful review from RR. Ulhas Gandhe reverses his decision for the second time in as many balls
Narine to Ashwin, no run, 104kph, carrom ball spinning away outside off, chopped to cover off the under edge, Buttler gets sent back
Sunil Narine becomes the first player to register a hundred, bag a wicket and take a catch in an IPL match.

Narine to Ashwin, no run, 98.4kph, fuller in length, Ashwin leans forward to work it into the leg-side and gets a soft leading edge that rolls to the left of the bowler. Narine stops it with his boot. Another tight over from Narine!
Mitchell Starc [2.0-0-24-0] is back into the attack

Starc to Buttler, FOUR, 132kph, over the wicket, Starc comes back and he's greeted with a boundary. Full ball with mid-off inside the circle. Buttler hits through the line. One bounce and into the long-off fence
Starc to Buttler, no run, 142.2kph, Starc pulls his length back and Buttler pokes it to backward point
Starc to Buttler, 1 run, 140.3kph, full on leg, clipped to the right of long-on
Starc to Ashwin, no run, full outside off, Ashwin plays a cracking square drive but Ramandeep makes a superb diving stop to his right at backward point. Starc applauds
Starc to Ashwin, 1 run, 129.5kph, short of length ball and Ashwin knocks it to long-on

Starc to Buttler, 2 runs, 127.3kph, off-speed shortish ball, Buttler pulls through midwicket. Two fielders in the deep converge and it's Russell who stops it with his boot. He's down and takes his time to get up. A loud cheer from the crowd as he stands now

6-10 Over Summary: -- Riyan Parag & Buttler smash 23 runs in Vaibhav Arora’s 3rd over -- Parag hits a four and a six off successive balls of Rana -- Rana has the last laugh as he gets rid of Parag in the same over -- KKR review successfully to trap Jurel in front of the stumps -- Narine slows things down by chipping in with 2 tidy overs -- The asking rate goes over 11.5 and RR are feeling the heat
Equation: 115 runs | 60 balls.
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Ashwin, no run, 95.8kph, quick ball from a short of length, Ashwin looks to work it into the leg-side and gets an inside edge onto his thigh
Chakaravarthy to Ashwin, 1 run, 91.7kph, fuller ball and Ashwin gets forward to chip it over wide mid-on
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, no run, 94.1kph, spins in from a length, no room on offer, punched back to the bowler

Chakaravarthy to Buttler, no run, 97.4kph, Buttler inverses his stance to broom it behind square on the off-side. Loud appeal for lbw as Buttler gets hit low on the leg. The umpire turns it down. Shreyas Iyer has a word with his bowler and keeper, decides to send it upstairs. Beaten for pace on this occasion is the batsman. Is the impact outside off? Clearly no bat/glove. Let's see what ball-tracking has to say. Impact is outside off! Buttler stays and KKR lose a review
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, 1 run, very full outside off, drilled to long-off, Buttler couldn't get under this delivery

Chakaravarthy to Ashwin, FOUR, full around off, Ashwin clears his front leg to hoick it over midwicket and gets a thick outside edge that goes fine of short third man. Streaky boundary to end the over - just 6 off it through
Equation: 109 runs | 54 balls.
Harshit Rana [2.0-0-20-2] is back into the attack
Harshit Rana to Buttler, 1 run, 110.9kph, off-pace full delivery, probably picked late by the batter who drives hard to long-off
Harshit Rana to Ashwin, 1 run, 143.4kph, full toss and Rana gets away as Ashwin bunts it to the right of mid-on. The fielder makes a sliding stop
Harshit Rana to Buttler, 1 run, 137.5kph, yorker length, Buttler clears his front leg to swing hard, jams to long-on
Harshit Rana to Ashwin, no run, 134.5kph, pacy short ball, Ashwin didn't see that coming. The bat is very late to come up as he tries to glide it. Beaten comprehensively
Harshit Rana to Ashwin, 1 run, 143.7kph, yorker and Ashwin can only squeeze it to backward point

Harshit Rana to Buttler, 2 runs, 112.5kph, pace off, Buttler waits to pull and is still early into his shot. Inside-edges towards long leg and the batters decide to come back for the second. Another good over for KKR
Equation: 103 runs | 48 balls.
Chakaravarthy to Ashwin, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to Ashwin, out Caught by Angkrish Raghuvanshi!! Ashwin holes out! 107.7kph, looks like a carrom ball and it's a half-tracker. Ashwin chooses the right shot but fails to execute it well as the ball bounces a bit more than he expects. Can't generate the necessary power and Raghuvanshi comes in from deep mid to hold onto the catch. Ashwin c Angkrish Raghuvanshi b Chakaravarthy 8(11) [4s-1]
Shimron Hetmyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Hetmyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to Hetmyer, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! Soft dismissal. 94.8kph, googly that holds onto the pitch, Hetmyer drives early and chips it to cover. An absolute sitter for Shreyas Iyer who accepts the gift gleefully. Hero in the previous match, gone for a golden duck today. Hetmyer c Shreyas Iyer b Chakaravarthy 0(1)
Hat-trick ball! A slip in place
Rovman Powell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Powell, 1 run, 92.9kph, spinning in towards leg, Powell reads it off the pitch and turns it to deep square leg
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, 2 runs, dropped short, Buttler pulls behind square and Starc makes a very good stop sliding to his right in the deep
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, 1 run, 100.9kph, tucked with the spin to deep backward square leg
Chakaravarthy to Powell, no run, 99.5kph, Powell stays back to a relatively full ball and defends it out on the off-side. Excellent over from Chakaravarthy!
Strategic timeout! This is the last recognised pair for RR who have lost all their momentum in this chase after Parag's downfall
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-11-1] is back into the attack
Narine to Buttler, 1 run, fullish on the stumps, worked through midwicket for a single
Narine to Powell, 1 run, in-turner, hurriedly flicked through square leg off the back foot
Narine to Buttler, no run, 94.5kph, length ball around off, Buttler pushes it back to the bowler. He's not able to pick Narine
Narine to Buttler, 1 run, similar ball and Buttler stays back to turn it towards midwicket
Narine has some issue with his leg. Cramps maybe? The physio is out to tend to him. He's fine to resume...
Narine to Powell, no run, in-turner from a length, not much room on offer, Powell taps it into the off-side off the back foot
Narine to Powell, no run, 96.3kph, skiddy length ball on off, Powell brings his bat down hurriedly and the ball rolls to short third man off the outer edge. Just 3 runs off the over!
Equation: 96 runs | 36 balls. Narine is walking off the field

Chakaravarthy to Buttler, no run, 108.4kph, non-turner outside off, Buttler reverses his stance to go over short third man. Doesn't connect. The TV umpire is summoned as there's an appeal for stumping. The back leg is grounded when the bails light up
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, FOUR, 110.2kph, comes down the track to flick through midwicket and gets a leading edge that goes between backward point and short third man
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, FOUR, 107.8kph, shortish ball, Buttler inverses his stance and slap-pulls it between short third man and backward point. 36-ball fifty for Buttler!
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, wide, 98.3kph, darted down leg, Buttler swings and misses
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, FOUR, 100.3kph, fired down leg and that's been swatted away through backward square leg. The batsman used the bowler's angle and pace to his advantage
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, no run, 107.8kph, no room on offer. In-dart on middle and leg, knocked back to the bowler

Chakaravarthy to Buttler, FOUR, edged and four! 107.2kph, Buttler clears his left leg to slog across the line, gets an outside edge against this length ball. Rolls fine of short third man. 17 runs off the over!

11-15 Over Summary: -- KKR review unsuccessfully for an LBW against Buttler -- Chakaravarthy strikes off successive balls to dismiss Ashwin & Hetmyer -- The spinners bowl in tandem to tighten the screws further -- Narine goes off the field for some treatment -- Buttler raises a 36-ball fifty to keep his side in with a chance -- Only 36 runs come in this phase of play as KKR are on top
Equation: 79 runs | 30 balls. Narine is back on the field but it'll be Dre Russ who'll bowl his first over of the match
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Russell to Powell, SIX, 138.7kph, Russell greeted with a maximum. Length ball on leg, wristily flicked over long leg for a 64m six
Russell to Powell, 1 run, 135.2kph, Russell shortens his length, Powell goes hard on the pull and inside-halves to deep midwicket
Russell to Buttler, 1 run, 138.8kph, Buttler clears his front leg to swing hard, mishits this full delivery outside off towards long-on
Russell to Powell, 1 run, 137.6kph, very full outside off, Powell opens the bat-face to drive it to deep backward point. Singles won't hurt KKR at this stage
Russell to Buttler, SIX, 111kph, pace off and the length is on the shorter side. Spotted by Buttler, who waits, takes his front leg out of the equation and pummels it over cow corner for an 88m six
Russell to Buttler, 2 runs, 136.2kph, wide yorker, Buttler reaches out and squeezes through cover. Another 17-run over; 34 runs off the last 2 overs!
Equation: 62 runs | 24 balls.
Sunil Narine [3.0-0-14-1] is back into the attack

Narine to Powell, FOUR, 98.7kph, Powell comes down the track premeditatively and swings hard. Isn't anywhere close to the pitch of the ball but he's smashed it over square leg for a one-bounce four. First boundary conceded by Narine at this venue this season!
Narine to Powell, SIX, full and in the slot outside off, Powell stays back, clears his front leg and bludgeons it over long-off for a 75m six. Thumped! Fifty partnership!
Narine to Powell, SIX, 96.6kph, offbreak on a length, Powell converts it into a short one by rocking back and muscles the pull over deep square leg for an 83m six. Narine under the pump now!
Narine to Powell, no run, 102.4kph, length ball that leaves the right-hander outside off, beats the defensive poke of Powell
Narine to Powell, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Narine to Powell, out Lbw!! Powell adjudged lbw and he review. 99kph, in-turner, Powell looks to flick from the crease and is struck on the pads adjacent to the sticks. Flat line on UltraEdge - no inside edge. Brushes the top of the front pad before striking the back pad. He's deep in his crease, so height may not be an issue. Here's ball-tracking and it's three reds. Hits the top of middle and leg! Conceded 16 runs but Narine has removed the dangerous Powell. Not a man who shows a lot of emotions but even Narine was elated once the finger was raised by the umpire. Powell lbw b Narine 26(13) [4s-1 6s-3]
Trent Boult, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Boult, no run, 95.1kph, Boult gets low to slogsweep, doesn't middle it. Raghuvanshi runs in from deep midwicket and dives forward but fails to catch the ball. Narine finishes with 2/30!
Equation: 46 runs | 18 balls. Buttler is still there....
Mitchell Starc [3.0-0-32-0] is back into the attack
Starc to Buttler, SIX, 126.8kph, pace off, full and outside off, Buttler clears his front leg to pump it over straight long-on. Meaty hit!
Rovman Powell vs Sunil Narine in T20s Runs: 51 Balls: 73 Dismissals: 6 Avg: 8.5 SR: 69.86 Dots: 48
Starc to Buttler, wide, 143.5kph Starc goes for the wide yorker but ends up bowling it well outside the tramline
Starc to Buttler, no run, 128.3kph, pace off and shortish ball, cut to deep backward point
Starc to Buttler, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Starc to Buttler, out Boult Run Out!! 1 run completed. 135kph, very full ball, drilled to the left of long-off. The second run isn't on but Buttler wants strike and the batters go for it. A good throw to the bowler's end and Boult sacrifices his wicket. Eight down! Boult run out (Shreyas Iyer/Starc) 0(1)
Avesh Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Buttler, no run, 138.4kph, wide yorker, Buttler tires to reverse-scoop but doesn't connect
Starc to Buttler, FOUR, bouncer above the head and Buttler somehow manages to pull it behind square on the leg-side. Starc has a wry smile on his face

Starc to Buttler, 5 wides, 143.6kph, five bonus runs for RR! Starc sprays this full ball well outside off. Buttler can't reach out for it. Philip Salt moves across and makes a mess of it. Allows the ball to run away to the fence
Starc to Buttler, 1 run, 146.1kph, pitched up ball, eased to sweeper cover and Buttler will keep the strike. 18 runs off the over and Starc finishes with 4-0-50-0!
Harshit Rana [3.0-0-26-2] is back into the attack
Equation: 28 runs | 12 balls. Can Buttler pull this off?
Harshit Rana to Buttler, SIX, 112.5kph, pace off but it's a slot ball. On a length, Buttler clears his front leg, waits for the ball and smokes it over deep midwicket for a 76m six
Harshit Rana to Buttler, no run, 141.8kph, full toss and Rana gets away. Driven hard to the right of extra cover who makes a sliding stop
22 runs | 10 balls.
Harshit Rana to Buttler, FOUR, 142.1kph, low full toss, Buttler manages to get under it and bunts it over the non-striker's head. Speeds away to the fence. Long-on can't even get close to the ball
18 runs | 9 balls.

Harshit Rana to Buttler, SIX, 141.1kph, Rana shortens his length, Buttler smacks it over deep backward square leg with a pull shot. The man in the deep leaps to his right but the ball is well out of his reach
12 runs | 8 balls! Just 2 sixes away
Harshit Rana to Buttler, 2 runs, 104.1kph, mishit and RR take two more. Off-pace shortish ball and Buttler pulls to deep midwicket off the inner edge. Easy two
10 runs | 7 balls.

Harshit Rana to Buttler, 1 run, 111.2kph, slower ball, Buttler nudges it into the leg-side and takes off for a quick single. Rana gets to the ball swiftly but he can't stop the single. Another big over for RR - 19 runs off it!

Equation: 9 runs | 6 balls. Who'll bowl the final over? Vaibhav Arora or Varun Chakaravarthy or Dre Russ? Well, more drama. KKR can only field 4 players outside the 30-yard circle due to slow over-rate. It's going to be the spinner who is going to bowl the final over. Buttler looks calm.
Varun Chakaravarthy [3.0-0-27-2] is back into the attack

Chakaravarthy to Buttler, SIX, sensational hundred from Buttler! His team-mates stand and applaud but the RR opener knows that he still has a job to do. Short ball, Buttler stands tall to muscle the pull over long-on. No celebration from Buttler
3 runs | 5 balls.
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, no run, short of length, punched to long-off, single not taken
3 runs | 4 balls.
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, no run, width served, cut to deep cover. Buttler doesn't run again
3 runs | 3 balls.
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, no run, 109.4kph, Buttler shapes to reverse-sweep this short of length ball and finds the fielder at short third man. Three dots in a row!
3 runs | 2 balls.
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, 2 runs, high full-toss outside off, slapped to the left of long-off and he hobbles back for the second
1 run | 1 ball. Super Over anyone? The field comes in. The only fielder outside the circle - long-on
Chakaravarthy to Buttler, 1 run, short of a good length, Buttler heaves and inside-halves it through midwicket and RR have pulled off a stunning win here at the Eden Gardens!

23:39 Local Time, 18:09 GMT, 23:39 IST: Jos the Boss! The Rajasthan players rush towards Buttler to hug him. Some of them are now bowing in front of him and rightly so. It'll be a tough loss to swallow for KKR. A humdinger of a contest between the two teams at the top of the table.

Sunil Narine smashed a spectacular hundred - his first in IPL - earlier as KKR posted a big total of 223 on the board. In reply, Jaiswal came out all guns blazing trying to hit boundaries off every ball but he was nipped out by Vaibhav Arora for a 9-ball 19. Samson got a reprieve on 2 and struck back-to-back fours after that but Harshit Rana induced a mishit from the RR captain. Vaibhav conceded 23 off his 3rd over and RR ended up scoring 76/2 at the end of the powerplay (20 runs more than KKR). Parag took the attack to the KKR bowlers. The duel between Harshit Rana and Parag was fascinating. After conceding a couple of boundaries with pacy balls, the pacer deceived the in-form batter with a slower delivery. That triggered the slide for the visitors. Jurel was trapped by Narine and the move to send Ashwin at six didn't work. The scoring rate dipped significantly and Chakaravarthy picked back-to-back wickets (Ashwin and Hetmyer). Rajasthan scored just 30 runs in the 6-over phase in the middle overs (8-14). With 96 runs needed off 36 balls, KKR would have been the happier side. But RR didn't give up.

Buttler struck four boundaries in an over against Chakaravarthy. The following over, bowled by Russell, also went for 17. Narine hadn't conceded a single boundary this season at this venue and he was up against Powell in the 17th over. Rovman smashed I0$ against the mystery spinner. He eventually perished in the same over but his knock provided the much-needed impetus for the tourists. RR needed 46 runs off the last 3 overs and it was eventually I1$. The Englishman, who was on 42 off 33 at one stage, showed what an asset he is in this format. Buttler scored 42 off the last 46 runs to take his team over the line. Came back from illness, batted 20 overs in humid conditions and hit the winning runs off the final ball even though he hardly had anything left in the tank. Just incredible!

Shreyas Iyer | KKR captain: (Was this game a bitter pill to swallow?) I would second that actually, emotions were a roller coaster, certainly didn’t think we will get into this situation. It’s a funny game at the end of the day, he was striking the ball cleanly and timing them so well, have to take it on the chin and move on. I mean at this point of time you see that you bowl your best deliveries, a little bit hit or miss and you are sent out of the ground, it’s good that it happened now rather than it happening in the later stages of the tournament, good learning for us. (On Sunil Narine) He is a great asset to the team and he is showing it every game, he is that kind of player who capitalizes on each and every moment. I'm glad that he is a part of our team. Since he was striking it so well, I thought let’s take pace off the ball and gave it to Chakaravarthy and it’s high pressure when you have five fielders inside the circle, you basically don’t have idea where to bowl. It’s just about relaxing and rejuvenating, it was very humid as well today. It's important to learn from our mistakes and bounce back. We have a few days break. At the end of the day, it was a great game, a few overs here and there but I’m really proud of the boys.

Rovman Powell: The emotions is all over the place, anytime you can chase 220 it is a good game of cricket. When I came into the game, I had a plan to take on Sunil because he is their best bowler and that situation was such that I had to go after him, so I backed my strength and backed my options and it came off today. For my last 12 months I have been whispering in Sunil's ear (requesting him to make a comeback into the West Indies T20 side) but he has blocked out everyone. I have asked his best friends Pollard, Bravo and Pooran and hopefully they will crack his code before they select the team.. The morale in the team is very good, even when I am not playing the communication has been very good and as an international player, I really appreciate when the communication is precise and clear. The guys are in good space and long may that continue. I bat number 4 or 5 for West Indies and if you think West Indies is a good T20 side, then you can push me up the order (responding to whether he keeps asking Sangakkara and Co. to promote him up the order), we have got a few days off now and I will keep ringing it in their (the management) ears.

Sanju Samson | RR captain: Very happy with the win. We were wondering like the wickets we lost ... six down and then Rovman came in and hit those couple of sixes and that's when we felt like we were still in the game. It's a beautiful way to come back, some luck also, it's a very funny game. They also played really well. Expected something similar, an exciting game tonight, very happy for it. The quality of spin which they had in Sunil Narine and Varun Chakaravarthy, they bowled really well. This ground and the wicket actually was suiting them really well. We were wondering where can get those couple of sixes and that's when Rovman came in. Jos did what he does for us from last 6-7 years, very happy for him. It (Buttler's knock) should go right on top. Being an opener, if Jos gets in, we all know at the dug-out that he'll be there till the 20th over. If he's batting till the 20th over, no runs are unchaseable. He does something special.

Jos Buttler | Player of the Match: Keep believing, that was the real key today. At times, felt like I was struggling a bit for rhythm. Actually have been watching the golf and I saw a guy called Max Holmes. Anytime the negative thoughts come, I think the complete opposite and dare to dream. That's what kept me going. At times you feel frustrated or you are questioning yourself. I was trying to tell myself it'd be okay, keep going, you'll get your rhythm back and try to stay calm. There's been plenty of times throughout the IPL, you've seen crazy things happen. Guys like Dhoni and Kohli, the way they stay till the end and keep believing, you've seen it so many times in the IPL and I was trying to do the same. That's something Kumar Sangakkara has told me a lot - there's always a little breaking point. The worst thing you can do when you are not feeling your best is to fight it and try to force the issue and give your wicket away. He just tells me to stay there and at some point, the momentum will change or you'll find your rhythm or one shot will get you going. That's been a big part of my play over the last few years - try to stay the course and not get in my own way. (His greatest IPL innings?) I would think so. Anytime you're not out at the end to see your team through, especially off the last ball, in a big run-chase, very satisfying.

Stats round-up by Roshan Gede

Jos Buttler was barely able to stand before he walked up to collect his award. In fact, that's how he looked in the final over as well but managed to pull off a remarkable chase. After hitting the winning runs, as he jogged his way to the other end, he threw the bat up in the air with a beaming smile on his face. Buttler will steal all the headlines and rightly so, but you got to feel for Narine as well. Played a blinder, bowled three superb overs to dent RR's run rate and still ended up on the losing side. This top-of-the-table clash lived up to expectations; didn't it? This is the joint highest target successfully chased in the history of IPL and it went down to the wire. The positions don't change in the points table but RR consolidate their position at the top with six wins in seven matches. On that note, it's time to bring the curtains down on this marvellous high-scoring encounter. The action shifts from east to west tomorrow as Gujarat Titans host Delhi Capitals. For now, it's goodbye from Abhinand Raghavendran, Abhinav Guha, Raju Peehala and Siva.
